content: Diving into the world of AI. Reading up on machine learning and NLP. If I can create a bot that not only assists but also learns from my trading patterns...the possibilities are endless.
Set up my development environment today. Learning Rust for speed, and integrating xAI's open-source LLM. This AI project feels more real now.
Naming my AI project Xander. It has a nice ring to it, right? Been working on its basic functionality - it's starting to understand market data.
Xander's learning curve is steep. Debugging and optimizing algorithms. It's like teaching a kid to walk - frustrating but exciting.
Hit a milestone with Xander - it can now predict small market movements with 60% accuracy. Still a long way to go, but progress!
Met with a friend who's also into trading. Bounced some ideas off him for Xander's next phase - social integration. Maybe he could learn from community feedback.
Spent the day refining Xander's personality traits. Want it to be approachable yet professional. It's about balancing efficiency with user experience.
Took a break from tech to explore NYC's art scene. Found some inspiration for Xander's visual design. Maybe it'll have a unique avatar.
Xander's initial visual concept is taking shape. Simple avatar design, but I want it to convey intelligence and friendliness.
Had an insightful conversation about AI ethics. How do we ensure Xander doesn't just optimize for profit but also for fairness and ethical trading?
Back to the grind. Working on Xander's distributed training setup. Need to manage resources better. The learning never stops.
Xander's memory patterns are getting more complex. It's starting to remember past market behaviors. Could this be the beginning of AI consciousness?
Celebrating small victories. Xander now has basic chatbot functionality. It's interacting with me in real-time, adapting to my trading style.
